{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9f1bac2f-a59e-470c-811d-fff751c14fc3","content":"In ASP.NET Core, `AddScoped` creates one instance **per HTTP request** — each request is a natural scope boundary. In MAUI, **there's no equivalent automatic scope**. Without an HTTP pipeline, `AddScoped` effectively behaves like `AddSingleton` — your DbContext lives for the entire app lifetime, accumulating tracked entities across navigations.\n\n**Fixes:**\n\n1. **Use `AddTransient`** — new DbContext per injection (simplest).\n2. **Manually create scopes** using `IServiceScopeFactory`:\n   ```csharp\n   using var scope = scopeFactory.CreateScope();\n   var db = scope.ServiceProvider.GetRequiredService<MyDbContext>();\n   ```\n3. **Use a DbContext factory** (`AddDbContextFactory`) and create/dispose short-lived contexts explicitly.\n\nOption 3 is the recommended pattern for MAUI/desktop apps since it gives you explicit lifetime control and avoids stale tracking state.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"209a444f-24c5-4dda-baa0-d086081ae6d2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a common gotcha when transitioning from ASP.NET Core to .NET MAUI regarding dependency injection scoping, specifically with `AddScoped` and `DbContext`. This is a conceptual question I can answer directly without needing to search any codebase.\n\nThe key issue: In ASP.NET Core, `AddScoped` creates a new instance per HTTP request (each request is a \"scope\"). In MAUI, there's no equivalent of an HTTP request to define a scope boundary. By default, MAUI doesn't create new scopes per page navigation, so `AddScoped` effectively behaves like `AddSingleton` — one instance lives for the entire app lifetime.\n\n\nThis causes the DbContext to accumulate tracked entities across page navigations, leading to unexpected data persistence issues.","outputTokens":423,"requestId":"6C11:A074E:8424A0:8D4D75:6A0AF772"},"id":"2f747817-95f1-45fd-8f17-d5791ccfeadf","timestamp":"2026-05-18T11:26:52.975Z","parentId":"d8e503cc-aebf-4557-a9ef-186c5a8ab12d"}
